



# change in riqht panel - Scene Properties - Units - Unit Scale -> 0.001 --> en milimetros
# change in show overlays (up of coordinates) - Scale -> 0.001


1-9 # change view

mouse-left + g                          # grab
mouse-left + r                          # rotate
mouse-left + s                          # scale
mouse-left + [r,s] + [x,y,z]            # action on axis
mouse-left + [r,s] + shift + [xy,zy,xz] # action on 2 axis
mouse-left + r + Ctrl                   # rotate on precise
mouse-left + r + Ctrl + Shift           # rotate on precise more granuraly
mouse-Right                             # release selection 

To change an object, we need to enter Edit mode
mouse-left + Tab                        # enter Edit mode
select editing mode (icons beside Edit mode dropdown) between Vertex, Edge and Face.
mouse-left + E + [x,y,z]                # modify

merge... 
select + m

wireframe: see all edges
z + 4
a   # select all
a+a # deselect all

shift + d # duplicate selection, in edit mode, are the same object
shift + d # duplicate selection, in object mode, are the different object
ctrl + j  # merge selected object

to make face, select vertices or edges and press 'f'

